description.text: Competences the student acquires after the completion of Graduate university study are sufficient conditions for attending the programme of Postgraduate doctoral study at the Faculty of Civil Engineering, Architecture and Geodesy in Split, as well as for attending the same or similar programmes and Postgraduate specialist studies at other faculties of Civil Engineering in Croatia. The acquired learning outcomes enable the student to attend other postgraduate study programmes in the field of technical sciences.

entryRequirementsNote.text: The minimum educational requirement for enrolment into graduate university programmes is the completion of an undergraduate university programme. The university can allow students who have completed a professional programme to also enrol graduate university programmes, but they are allowed to set special requirements in these cases. The minimum educational requirement for enrolment into specialist graduate professional programmes is the completion of an undergraduate university programme or a professional programme (first cycle).

description.text: To knowledge and understanding that is founded upon and extends and/or enhances preceding qualifications level, and that provides a basis or opportunity for originality in developing and/or applying ideas, often within a research context.
To perform numerical modelling of structures (non-linear static and dynamic analysis of structures).
To clearly communicate own conclusions and develop learning skills for lifelong learning.
To manage investments and business in construction sector, to organise and plan construction work, and to perform public procurement for construction work.
To perform structural reliability assessment.
To participate in the construction of different types of structures and supervise design and construction work.
To evaluate dynamic characteristics of structures and perform calculation of structures resistant to earthquake.
To analyse and solve problems related to the stability of structures.
To apply knowledge and problem solving abilities in new environment within multidisciplinary contexts related to the field of study.

To design and perform engineering calculations of all types of structures (buildings, bridges, dams, silos, tunnels, hydrotechnical structures etc.) which are composed of different structural load bearing systems and different types of material (concrete, prestressed concrete, metal, timber, stone, masonry, composite, etc.)
To design the concrete mixture composition and its production technology.
To design and perform calculation of the fire resistance of structure.
To analyse and solve problems related to the durability of structures in different building stages: project design, construction and maintenance.
To integrate knowledge and handle complexity, and to formulate judgments with incomplete information, that include reflection on social and ethical responsibilities.
To design and perform calculation of geotechnical structures.
To evaluate production using standard indicators, make judgement on companies based on their balance sheets and assess investments.
To formulate equations of mathematical physics for engineering problems, and to solve them analytically or with numerical methods.
